        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>4000 models built between July 16, 1996 and August 30, 1996, and 2000 and 8000 models built
                    between July 16, 1996 and September 6, 1996 may have misaligned spot welds connecting the cab back
                    panel to the floor sill which will cause cracking and separation of the back panel. To repair the
                    defect, it has been determined that 3/16 inch stainless steel rivets should be installed in back
                    panel/floor sill flange to assure structural integrity of the cab.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
