        <svcproc svcproctype="afcrepair" graphiccount="1">
            <title>INSPECTION CRITERIA FOR CAB BACK PANEL AND FLOOR SILL SPOT WELDS</title>
            <svcsubproc>
                <title>High Mount Cab (2000, 8000 Models)</title>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Must have 80% (24 or more of 30) good spot welds (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690801">Full Nuggets</hotlnk>) across the bottom area (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690801">Zones 1, 2, and 3</hotlnk>) of back panel where back panel is spot
                        welded to floor sill.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9690801" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9690801" filename="../afcfigures/g9690801.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 1.</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">No more than 2 consecutive missing or poor spot welds (Partial or No Nugget) which
                        are in any one zone (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690801">see Diagram</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </step1>
            </svcsubproc>
            <svcsubproc>
                <title>Low Mount Cab (4000 Models)</title>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Must have 50% (15 or more of 30) good spot welds (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690801">Full Nuggets</hotlnk>) across the bottom area (Zones 1, 2, and 3) of
                        back panel where back panel is spot welded to floor sill.
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">No more than 3 consecutive missing or poor spot welds (Partial or No Nugget) in any
                        one zone (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690801">see Diagram</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <para>Cabs that meet the above inspection criteria need no repair. Cabs that do not meet the inspection
                    criteria must have the rivet kit installed.
                </para>
            </svcsubproc>
        </svcproc>
        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="0">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <svcsubproc>
                <title>Low Mount Cab (4000 Models)</title>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Under cab, inspect welds securing back panel to floor to determine need for repair.
                        If repair is required, complete repair Steps 2 through 11.
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Disconnect block heater wiring at cab.</para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Remove front section of driveshaft and support second section.</para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Loosen cab front mounting bolts, but do not remove.</para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Remove nuts from cab rear mounts between mount and cab.</para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Under the cab, use a frame stand and bottle jack to raise the cab approximately 1/2
                        inch to relieve tension from the cab rear mounts.
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Remove the wire harness from the cab rear crossmember and remove cab rear
                        crossmember and support brackets.
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Mark and center punch the holes in Zone 2 to be drilled, assuring rivets will
                        capture both flanges.
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Drill six .1935 diameter holes (#10 drill) in the back panel/floor sill flange.
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Install 6 rivets (Kit Part Number 8000786R91) in drilled holes.</para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Re-install all components to original position.</para>
                    <step2>
                        <para count="1">Tighten rear cab crossmember bolts to 110 to 120 ft-lbs. (149 to 163 Nm).</para>
                    </step2>
                    <step2>
                        <para count="1">Tighten front and rear cab mounting bolts to 80 to 85 ft-lbs. (108 to 115 Nm).
                        </para>
                    </step2>
                </step1>
            </svcsubproc>
            <svcsubproc>
                <title>High Mount Cab (2000 and 8000 Models)</title>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Under cab, inspect welds securing the back panel to floor to determine need for
                        repair. If repair is required, complete repair Steps 2 through 9.
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Loosen cab front mount, but do not remove bolts.</para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Remove nuts from cab rear mount between mount and cab.</para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Under cab, use a bottle jack, supported by the frame or crossmember to raise the cab
                        approximately 2 inches or until there is sufficient clearance to drill and install Huck rivets.
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Mark and center punch the holes in Zone 2 to be drilled, assuring rivets will
                        capture both flanges.
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Drill six .1935 diameter holes (#10 drill) in the back panel/floor sill flange.
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Install 6 rivets (Kit Part Number 8000786R91).</para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Re-install all components to original position.</para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Tighten all cab mount bolts to 80 to 85 ft-lbs. (108 to 115 Nm).</para>
                </step1>
            </svcsubproc>
        </svcproc>
